==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Atheism
<hw>A"the*ism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>ath⟦eacute⟧isme</ets>. See <er>Atheist</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The disbelief or denial of the existence of a God, or supreme
intelligent Being.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Atheism</qex> is a ferocious system, that leaves nothing
above us to excite awe, nor around us to awaken tenderness.</q>
<rj><qau>R. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Atheism</qex> and pantheism are often wrongly confounded.</q>
<rj><qau>Shipley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Godlessness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Atheist</ent>⟦br⟧
